ACTIVITY 1: Demand Creation in Faith Infrastructures and Communities
Only countries that received Faith and Community Initiative (FCI) funding should complete these narratives.

1) Did the IP or IPs participate in meetings with other IPs/sub-awardees/Parent Bodies at least quarterly? Name the clearly defined action items that were the outcome of the partner meeting. Are there protocols in place for managing roles and responsibilities of the partners?
2) What types of faith leaders/workers (pastors/imams, expert clients, CHWs, peer educators, nurses, clinicians, lay workers) received support (monetary or non-monetary) for disseminating the New Messages of Hope based on PEPFAR research insights, in faith communities?
3) Describe the number and types of media that were used to disseminate New Messages of Hope by Parent Body or inter-faith structure (e.g., social media platforms, radio, or billboard spots)?
4) Were there any challenges disseminating the 6 topics from New Messages of Hope using Parent Body (national to local) structures, or inter-faith (district) structures?
5) In priority SNUs for case-finding, please document the type of congregation (by religious affiliation or denomination) and number of congregations that deployed/received New Messages of Hope during sermons, messages, or programs. How did performance compare with targets in the work-plan, for number of congregations reached with 3-6 topics from New Messages of Hope?
Required
ACTIVITY 2: Expanding Targeted Prevention, HIV Self-Testing, Index Testing, Linkage, Retention and Viral Load Suppression
Only countries that received Faith and Community Initiative (FCI) funding should complete these narratives.

1) What types of faith leaders/workers (pastors/imams, expert clients, CHWs, peer educators, nurses, clinicians, lay workers, etc.) received support (monetary or non-monetary) for HTS? This includes support for disseminating HIV self-tests and supporting linkage and retention in faith communities?
2) What number of HIV tests and/or of self-tests were distributed through faith community/FBO sources?
3) What monitoring approaches were used for HTS, including those who used self-tests to track linkage to facility for confirmatory testing and ARV initiation, or for prevention?
4) What number of persons with positive test results, including from self-tests from FBO sources, reported to a facility for confirmatory testing or verification?
5) Please describe the number of congregations (by religious affiliation or denomination) that developed and deployed support for linkage and retention. How did the number of persons receiving support for linkage/retention compare with targets in the work plan?
Required
ACTIVITY 3: Decreasing Stigma and Non-Adherence Related to Faith Healing in Congregations
Only countries that received Faith and Community Initiative (FCI) funding should complete these narratives.

1) What type of faith structures (e.g., national, regional, district, and zonal offices; local church congregations; district interfaith councils, etc.) newly implemented evidence-informed interventions or educational programs?
2) Which evidence-informed interventions or educational programs were used (by religious affiliation or denomination)?
3) Were there any challenges to implementing these interventions or programs within faith structures? Were any religious groups resistant to these interventions? If yes, please describe.
4) How did performance compare with targets in the work plan, for number of congregations reached with interventions or programming?
